1 Bayesian Network: Example

For this example we will use the bnlearn package in R to illustrate the use of Bayesian Network. We will use R to create the network illustrated by the figure below.

Start by loading the bnlearn library

library(bnlearn)
## 
## Attaching package: 'bnlearn'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     sigma

Create the names of the nodes for the network

vname = c("Pol","Smk","Can","Xry","Dys")

Attach the nodes to a graph

e = empty.graph(vname)

Create the connection(relation) between the nodes. Then, attach the connection to the graph

arc.set = matrix(c("Pol","Smk","Can","Can","Can","Can","Xry","Dys"),
ncol = 2, dimnames = list (NULL,c("from","to")))
arcs(e) = arc.set

Create the conditional probability tables for each node

cptPol = matrix(c(0.9,0.1), ncol = 2, dimnames = list(NULL, c("low","high")))
cptSmk = matrix(c(0.3,0.7), ncol = 2, dimnames = list(NULL, c("true","false")))
cptCan = c(0.30,0.70,0.001,0.999,0.95,0.05,0.2,0.8)
dim(cptCan) = c(2,2,2)
dimnames(cptCan) = list("Can" = c("true","false"),"Smk" = c("true","false"),"Pol" = c("low","high"))
cptXry = c(0.9,0.1,0.2,0.8)
dim(cptXry) = c(2,2)
dimnames(cptXry) = list("Xry" = c("true","false"), "Can" = c("true","false"))
cptDys = c(0.65,0.35,0.3,0.7)
dim(cptDys) = c(2,2)
dimnames(cptDys) = list("Dys" = c("true","false"), "Can" = c("true","false"))

Attach the CPTs to the graph.

dfit = custom.fit(e, dist = list(Pol = cptPol, Smk = cptSmk, Can = cptCan, Xry= cptXry, Dys = cptDys))
dfit

Now we are ready to query the network. The R code below are calculating the following probabilities:

  • P(Polution = low|Cancer = true)
  • P(Polution = low|Cancer = true;Dysponea = false)
  • P(Xray = positive|Cancer = true;Dysponea = false)
  • P(Xray = negative|Cancer = true;Dysponea = false)
  • P(Xray = negative|Polution = high; Smoker = true)
  • P(Xray = positive|Polution = high; Smoker = true)
cpquery(dfit,event=(Pol == "low"), evidence=(Can == "true"))
## [1] 0.624183
cpquery(dfit,event=(Pol == "low"), evidence=(Can == "true") & (Dys=="false"))
## [1] 0.6585366
cpquery(dfit,event=(Xry == "true"), evidence=(Can == "true") & (Dys=="false"))
## [1] 0.9281768
cpquery(dfit,event=(Xry == "false"), evidence=(Can == "true") & (Dys=="false"))
## [1] 0.09852217
cpquery(dfit,event=(Xry == "false"), evidence=(Pol == "high") & (Smk=="true"))
## [1] 0.106383
cpquery(dfit,event=(Xry == "true"), evidence=(Pol == "high") & (Smk=="true"))
## [1] 0.8830409

2 Homework

For the homework, you will use the bnlearn library and R to create bayesian network described by the figure below.

Your tasks

  1. Submit the list of command you have used to create the network, make sure your CPT tables are correct.

  • P(WG = true|S = true;W = true)

  • P(WG = false|SR = false;W = true)
  1. submit a list of the commands you have used to answer the above probabilities calculation along with the results of the commands
